<TITLE> BDR seizes 1873 Phensidyl bottles </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jaipurhat, May 13 (bdnews24.com)A Bangladesh Rifles highway patrol on Wednesday seized 1,873 bottles of Phensidyl, a syrupy expectorant abused as addictive drug, from a truck at Shimultali on Jaipurhat-Hili highway. None was arrested though. Lt Col Rafiqul Haque, Jaipurhat 3 Rifles Battalion commander, said the huge lot of Phensidyl bottles smuggled in from across the border nearby was being transported to Dhaka in a truck. Seeing the BDR men approaching, the smugglers left their vehicle and cargo at Shimultali under Panchbibi upazila. A case is being filed, he said.
